subSubSection.paragraph:
Colouration and pattern (
Figure 1C
): Carapace dark chestnut-brown; integument punctated, covered with punctures forming radiating striae. Carapace, chelicerae and sternum dark reddish brown. Coxae, trochanters and femora dark brown (except femora I–II brown, distally yellow); patellae, tibiae, metatarsi and tarsi orange. Opisthosoma ovoid; dorsum of opisthosoma with pattern consisting of paired, medially connected patches, followed by four chevrons and white area above spinnerets on dark grey background. Dorsal scutum orange-brown, wider in front than behind, posterior margin straight, occupying approximately half of opisthosoma length.

Colouration and pattern (
Figure 2F
): Carapace dark chestnut-brown; integument punctate, with large pits forming striae. Fovea obsolete. Chelicerae, sternum, labium and gnathocoxae dark reddish-brown. Legs I–II brown, femora slightly darker than other segments, tibiae orange-brown distally; legs III–IV orange-brown except femora dark brown, distally pale yellow. Opisthosoma elongate-ovoid; dorsum grey, with paired, irregular-shaped patches, followed by four chevrons and white area above spinnerets.
